rest_of_day_open:
I think this will be a normal "lockdown" week. My son will go to work, the other one will do his online classes and I will spend what feels like most of my time cooking for them!

This will be an ordinary week, at least until the new washing machine arrives on Thursday.
critical_positive: My partner was warm and open. It would have been a better conversation if we had had a prompt or topic to launch the conversation from. Other than geography, we didn't have much in common but I think our conversation was easy going in spite of that. He was a nice guy but as a conversation pair we needed a bit of direction
critical_negative: We had little in common and that made things awkward and a little stiff. However, even if we had had more in common a conversation prompt would have helped. There wasn't a clear idea of what to talk about. We needed clearer directions. We also were befuddled by the timer clock and real-time not syncing up. We think that may have been part of the point

rest_of_day_open: I imagine the rest of my week will be fun and enjoyable. I plan to spend time with my girlfriend at her place. I picture us eating food together and watching tv shows. I also have my home showing scheduled for later this week for which I am looking forward.
critical_positive: I think what worked well was that my conversation partner had plenty of questions to ask me. I felt like she was sincerely interested in a lot of what I had to say. We both had knowledge about a wide range of subjects. Overall, I thought my partner was enjoyable to talk with.
critical_negative: There wasn't much that did not go well in the conversation I just had. I think one think was that during the start of the conversation, we were not quite sure about the subject matter this conversation was to be about. I think we also kept thinking about how much time we had to keep talking for.
